WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:05.000
Gettysburg Address by Abraham Lincoln. Read by Jim Cadwell for LibriVox.org.

00:05.000 --> 00:16.000
Four score and seven years ago our fathers brought forth on this continent, a new nation,

00:16.000 --> 00:24.000
conceived in Liberty, and dedicated to the proposition that all men are created equal.

00:24.000 --> 00:36.000
Now we are engaged in a great civil war, testing whether that nation, or any nation so conceived and so dedicated, can long endure.

00:36.000 --> 00:41.000
We are met on a great battle-field of that war.

00:41.000 --> 00:50.000
We have come to dedicate a portion of that field, as a final resting place for those who here gave their lives that that nation might live.

00:50.000 --> 00:54.000
It is altogether fitting and proper that we should do this.

00:54.000 --> 01:05.500
But, in a larger sense, we can not dedicate -- we can not consecrate -- we can not hallow -- this ground.

01:05.500 --> 01:17.500
The brave men, living and dead, who struggled here, have consecrated it, far above our poor power to add or detract.

01:17.500 --> 01:25.500
The world will little note, nor long remember what we say here, but it can never forget what they did here.

01:25.500 --> 01:36.500
It is for us the living, rather, to be dedicated here to the unfinished work which they who fought here have thus far so nobly advanced.

01:36.500 --> 01:53.000
It is rather for us to be here dedicated to the great task remaining before us -- that from these honored dead we take increased devotion

01:53.000 --> 02:00.000
to that cause for which they gave the last full measure of devotion --

02:00.000 --> 02:08.500
that we here highly resolve that these dead shall not have died in vain --

02:08.500 --> 02:15.500
that this nation, under God, shall have a new birth of freedom --

02:15.500 --> 02:25.500
and that government of the people, by the people, for the people, shall not perish from the earth.

02:25.500 --> 02:30.000
[End of reading. This LibriVox recording is in the public domain.]
